Pre-Game Insights: India started the competition with a thrilling win against Pakistan and a clinical display against Netherlands.
South Africa's scoring rate in the tournament is over 11 runs per over.
The Optus Stadium has an average first innings score of 142 and the highest score registered batting first is 208 by England.
Virat Kohli vs Wayne Parnell is highlighted as a key player battle.
Suryakumar Yadav vs Kagiso Rabada is another anticipated contest.
Quinton de Kock vs Bhuvneshwar Kumar is expected to be a significant matchup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Optus Stadium has not hosted many T20Is, making it a challenging venue for batters.
Head-to-head record: India has won 13 out of 23 matches against South Africa.
